        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/e19adc/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-02-27T02:15:33.154Z",
        "cooked": "<p>And the rest of the instructions worked as well.</p>\n<p>One slight hurdle was the realisation that after creatng the empty backup in Molly and merging in the data from signal-desktop, I would not get Molly to import this backup unless I deleted the app’s user data to start Molly from a clean slate. It was a bit against my instinct to discard the work I’d just done to connect Molly to my account. But it seemed clear that this was what I’d have to, do so I went ahead and did it. And it turned out I didn’t have to do all the steps again (I didn’t have to receive another SMS message with a code). When I ran signalbackup-tools to merge the empty backup with the data from signal-desktop, there were many warnings and errors so I wasn’t sure how much history I would get to see in Molly. But then the end result turned out to be 1.5 GB in size so it became clear that the errors would be negligible. The end result is so much more restored history than I had expected before starting this thread.</p>\n<p>A slight caveat is that many or all groups are shown on top in Molly, including long-dormant ones, because the action of me joining these groups is shown as a new event. So all these groups have recent activity and are therefore shown on top of the chat list. Fortunately this rejoining event does not show up in signal-desktop so the sorting there is not distorted in this way. I guess I will just have to wait for new messages in other chats pushing these groups down the list in Molly, that’s okay.</p>\n<p>Again, thank you so much!</p>",
